	<ThingDef ParentName="Mashed_Ashlands_NixSteedThingBase">
		<defName>Mashed_Ashlands_NixSteed</defName>
		<label>nix-steed</label>
		<description>A large grazing horse-like insect native to calmer ashland regions. Closely related to the nix-hound, the nix-steed has a highly adapted proboscis which it uses to feed on nectar. Nix-steed tend to be quite temperamental, though some are brave enough to tame them for use as mounts.\n\n&lt;color=#E5E54C&gt;Nectarivore&lt;/color&gt;\nNix-steeds will consume nectar from ashland flowers when hungry. If none are available nearby, then they will consume plant matter instead.</description>
		<comps>
			<li Class="CompProperties_EggLayer">
				<eggFertilizedDef>Mashed_Ashlands_Egg_NixSteedFertilized</eggFertilizedDef>
				<eggFertilizationCountMax>1</eggFertilizationCountMax>
				<eggLayIntervalDays>3.3</eggLayIntervalDays>
				<eggProgressUnfertilizedMax>0.5</eggProgressUnfertilizedMax>
				<eggCountRange>1</eggCountRange>
			</li>
		</comps>
	</ThingDef>
